<body>
  <div class="page-container">
    <div class="content-card">
      <h1>About Gang Min Shin</h1>

      <p>
        Gang Min Shin completed a master's thesis titled
        <em>Pulsatile Waveform Analysis Using Diffuse Optical Flowmetry: A Study of the Prefrontal Cortex and Finger</em>
        in the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at DGIST.
      </p>

      <h2>Research Field</h2>

      <p>
        His research focuses on biomedical optics and diffuse optical flowmetry, especially the measurement and
        interpretation of human microcirculatory blood-flow signals using Multi-Mode Fiber Diffuse Speckle
        Contrast Analysis (MMF-DSCA).
      </p>

      <h2>Main Research Topic</h2>

      <p>
        The main research objective is to measure physiological information beyond simple mean blood-flow changes.
        For this purpose, Blood Flow Index (BFI), Blood Volume Index (BVI), pulsatile waveform features, and
        frequency-domain components are analyzed together.
      </p>

      <h2>Prefrontal Hemodynamic Study</h2>

      <p>
        One part of the research investigated prefrontal hemodynamic responses during cognitive-load tasks.
        Source-detector separation (SDS) channels were placed over the right prefrontal region, and the responses
        were evaluated in both the time domain and the frequency domain.
      </p>

      <h2>Peripheral Microcirculation Study</h2>

      <p>
        Another part of the research examined peripheral microcirculatory responses related to ST36 stimulation
        and the Cold Pressor Test (CPT). In this study, BFI, BVI, heart rate (HR), heart rate variability (HRV),
        and inter-beat interval (IBI) were analyzed to evaluate autonomic and vascular responses.
      </p>

      <h2>Keywords</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>MMF-DSCA: Multi-Mode Fiber Diffuse Speckle Contrast Analysis</li>
        <li>BFI: Blood Flow Index</li>
        <li>BVI: Blood Volume Index</li>
        <li>SDS: Source-Detector Separation</li>
        <li>HR: Heart Rate</li>
        <li>HRV: Heart Rate Variability</li>
        <li>CPT: Cold Pressor Test</li>
        <li>ST36: Zusanli acupoint</li>
      </ul>

